34
00:04:11,814 --> 00:04:12,940
(SWITCHING RADIO STATION)

35
00:04:13,015 --> 00:04:14,107
<i>(MONSTERS</i> PLAYING)

36
00:04:14,183 --> 00:04:16,981
<i>Situation's all critical</i>

37
00:04:17,053 --> 00:04:20,921
<i>You've got to look first before you go</i>

38
00:04:20,990 --> 00:04:22,890
<i>ERIC: It's Bella. Bella!</i>

39
00:04:23,292 --> 00:04:24,816
- Hi.
<i>- MIKE: I'm...</i>

40
00:04:27,029 --> 00:04:29,122
<i>JESSICA: Today's the big day, Bella.</i>

41
00:04:30,032 --> 00:04:31,795
<i>R and J</i> essay due.

42
00:04:32,101 --> 00:04:35,264
- Oh, yeah.
- Wherefore art thou, Bella?

43
00:04:35,338 --> 00:04:36,362
(ALL LAUGH)

44
00:04:36,439 --> 00:04:40,273
Let me take a picture of you guys.
My mom wants me to put together, like,

45
00:04:40,343 --> 00:04:41,469
a scrapbook full of memories.

46
00:04:41,544 --> 00:04:42,533
<i>ERIC: Oh.
MIKE: Cool. Yeah.</i>

47
00:04:42,612 --> 00:04:43,977
I take them. I'm not in them.

48
00:04:44,046 --> 00:04:45,445
- No, no, no, come here.
<i>- BELLA: Well, you are today.</i>

49
00:04:45,514 --> 00:04:46,879
You'll photoshop this
if my nose looks big, right?

50
00:04:46,949 --> 00:04:50,783
<i>ERIC: Don't worry, I'm in the picture.
No one will be looking at you guys.</i>

51
00:04:50,853 --> 00:04:52,252
<i>BELLA: That's good.</i>

52
00:04:52,955 --> 00:04:55,014
Oh, good. Cullen's here.

53
00:04:55,791 --> 00:04:57,019
(ERIC CHEERS WEAKLY)

54
00:04:58,027 --> 00:05:00,052
Well, talk to you later.

55
00:05:23,085 --> 00:05:24,780
- Happy birthday.
- Don't remind me.

56
00:05:24,854 --> 00:05:25,843
<i>EDWARD: Mmm.</i>

57
00:05:27,556 --> 00:05:30,116
Bella, your birth is definitely
something to celebrate.

58
00:05:30,192 --> 00:05:32,888
- Yeah, but my aging's not.
- Your aging?

59
00:05:33,329 --> 00:05:34,318
(CHUCKLES)

60
00:05:35,231 --> 00:05:38,029
I think 18 is a little young
to start worrying about that.

61
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:39,727
It's one year older than you.

62
00:05:39,802 --> 00:05:42,327
No, it isn't. I'm 109.

63
00:05:42,605 --> 00:05:45,768
Well, maybe I shouldn't be dating
such an old man.

64
00:05:45,841 --> 00:05:49,402
- Mmm.
- It's gross. I should be thoroughly repulsed.

65
00:05:49,478 --> 00:05:50,467
Uh-huh.

66
00:05:56,485 --> 00:05:57,679
(BOTH SIGHING)

67
00:06:01,257 --> 00:06:03,657
- We have to go to class.
- Okay.

68
00:06:05,294 --> 00:06:06,283
(EDWARD MOANS SOFTLY)

69
00:06:08,431 --> 00:06:09,955
Wait a second.

70
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,629
Someone wants you.

71
00:06:13,336 --> 00:06:15,236
<i>- JACOB: Bella!</i>
- Jacob!

72
00:06:15,771 --> 00:06:16,999
What?

73
00:06:18,774 --> 00:06:20,833
I'll leave you to talk.

74
00:06:25,047 --> 00:06:28,813
Hello, biceps! You know,
anabolic steroids are really bad for you.

75
00:06:28,884 --> 00:06:29,908
(JACOB LAUGHS)

76
00:06:29,985 --> 00:06:32,283
Well, I'm just filling out, Bella.

77
00:06:32,355 --> 00:06:35,791
You know, it wouldn't seem so drastic
if we hung out more.

78
00:06:36,292 --> 00:06:39,193
You should switch schools.
You can come hang out with the palefaces.

79
00:06:39,261 --> 00:06:42,697
I'm all right.
I prefer the rez school's exclusivity.

80
00:06:43,332 --> 00:06:45,800
They let any old riffraff into this place.

81
00:06:45,868 --> 00:06:47,961
- I see. Then why are you slumming it?
- Mmm-hmm.

82
00:06:48,037 --> 00:06:50,528
I was just buying a part for the Rabbit.

83
00:06:50,606 --> 00:06:53,131
You should really come
take a ride when it's done.

84
00:06:53,209 --> 00:06:54,574
Is it fast?

85
00:06:54,710 --> 00:06:55,699
Um.

86
00:06:56,512 --> 00:06:57,604
It's decent.

87
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,704
(BOTH LAUGH)

88
00:06:58,781 --> 00:07:01,045
- I'm kidding.
- Okay. Good.

89
00:07:01,784 --> 00:07:03,877
Hey, happy birthday.

90
00:07:05,454 --> 00:07:07,615
Your dad told my dad, so...

91
00:07:08,257 --> 00:07:10,225
Yeah, of course he did.

92
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:13,354
I saw this the other day
and thought of you.

93
00:07:14,964 --> 00:07:16,727
Catches bad dreams.

94
00:07:18,768 --> 00:07:20,759
That's kind of perfect.

95
00:07:22,972 --> 00:07:24,337
Thank you.

96
00:07:24,907 --> 00:07:26,340
No problem.

97
00:07:28,611 --> 00:07:29,703
- Good seeing you.
- Yeah, I'll see you later.

98
00:07:29,779 --> 00:07:30,905
Bye.

99
00:07:32,381 --> 00:07:36,078
So how come Jacob Black
gets to give you a gift and I don't?

100
00:07:37,253 --> 00:07:40,154
Because I have nothing to give back to you.

101
00:07:40,790 --> 00:07:43,657
Bella, you give me everything
just by breathing.

102
00:07:43,726 --> 00:07:44,715
(EXHALES)

103
00:07:45,628 --> 00:07:47,220
See? Thank you.

104
00:07:47,763 --> 00:07:49,890
- That's all I want.
<i>- ALICE: Bella!</i>

105
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:52,765
- Happy birthday!
- Shh, shh!

106
00:07:53,469 --> 00:07:55,164
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

107
00:07:56,405 --> 00:07:57,565
I thought I said no presents.

108
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,801
I've already seen you open it,
and guess what,

109
00:07:59,875 --> 00:08:01,308
you love it.

110
00:08:01,377 --> 00:08:04,175
You're gonna wear it tonight. Our place.

111
00:08:05,915 --> 00:08:08,907
Come on. Please? It'll be fun.

112
00:08:12,555 --> 00:08:14,921
- Okay. All right.
- Great!

113
00:08:14,990 --> 00:08:17,117
Okay, I'll see you at 7:00.

114
00:08:19,195 --> 00:08:22,264
Jasper, no fair with the mood control thing.

115
00:08:22,331 --> 00:08:23,320
(ALICE LAUGHS)

116
00:08:23,732 --> 00:08:26,292
Sorry, Bella. Happy...

117
00:08:27,636 --> 00:08:29,001
Never mind.

118
00:08:31,307 --> 00:08:34,572
You can't trust vampires. Trust me.

119
00:08:35,544 --> 00:08:37,603
<i>ROMEO: (ON VIDEO) O my love! My wife!</i>

120
00:08:38,414 --> 00:08:40,609
<i>Death, that hath sucked
the honey of thy breath</i>

121
00:08:40,683 --> 00:08:43,117
<i>hath had no power yet upon thy beauty.</i>

122
00:08:44,286 --> 00:08:46,151
<i>Thou art not conquered.</i>

123
00:08:47,623 --> 00:08:51,525
<i>Beauty's ensign yet is crimson
in thy lips and in thy cheeks.</i>

124
00:08:52,361 --> 00:08:55,228
<i>And death's pale flag is not advanced there.</i>

125
00:08:55,297 --> 00:08:57,265
<i>BELLA: I hate being celebrated.</i>

126
00:08:57,967 --> 00:09:00,902
<i>EDWARD: There are worse tragedies.
I mean, look at Romeo.</i>

127
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:03,939
Killed his true love out of sheer stupidity.

128
00:09:05,841 --> 00:09:06,933
<i>BELLA: Yeah.</i>

129
00:09:07,443 --> 00:09:09,604
Though I do envy him one thing.

130
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,539
<i>BELLA: Juliet is, like, perfect.</i>

131
00:09:13,616 --> 00:09:16,881
If you like
that obviously beautiful sort of thing.

132
00:09:16,952 --> 00:09:17,941
(EDWARD LAUGHS)

133
00:09:20,155 --> 00:09:23,090
Not the girl, the suicide.

134
00:09:27,029 --> 00:09:29,259
It's nearly impossible for...

135
00:09:30,733 --> 00:09:33,361
For some people.

136
00:09:36,038 --> 00:09:39,269
For humans, a little poison,

137
00:09:41,377 --> 00:09:43,368
a dagger to the heart.

138
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:47,240
There's so many different options.

139
00:09:50,519 --> 00:09:52,419
Why would you say that?

140
00:09:53,722 --> 00:09:56,213
Because I had to consider it once.

141
00:09:57,326 --> 00:09:58,350
(BELLA SCREAMING)

142
00:09:58,427 --> 00:10:00,452
<i>I didn't know if I'd get to you in time.</i>

143
00:10:01,096 --> 00:10:04,259
I had to come up with some kind of plan.

144
00:10:05,534 --> 00:10:07,229
What was the plan?

145
00:10:07,303 --> 00:10:10,761
That I'd go to Italy and provoke the Volturi.

146
00:10:11,607 --> 00:10:13,837
- The what?
- The Volturi.

147
00:10:13,909 --> 00:10:17,367
<i>MR. BERTY: Now, who'd like to repeat
the last few lines of iambic pentameter</i>

148
00:10:17,446 --> 00:10:20,006
just to show they were paying attention?

149
00:10:20,416 --> 00:10:21,815
Mr. Cullen?

150
00:10:22,117 --> 00:10:23,914
(INHALES DEEPLY)

151
00:10:24,853 --> 00:10:26,480
Yes, Mr. Berty.

152
00:10:29,224 --> 00:10:33,092
"O here will I set up my everlasting rest

153
00:10:35,097 --> 00:10:39,261
"and shake the yoke of inauspicious stars
from this world-wearied flesh.

154
00:10:40,102 --> 00:10:41,967
"Eyes, look your last.

155
00:10:42,571 --> 00:10:44,835
"Arms, take your last embrace!

156
00:10:45,808 --> 00:10:48,709
"And, lips, O you, the doors of breath,

157
00:10:49,378 --> 00:10:53,712
"seal with a righteous kiss a dateless
bargain to engrossing death!"

158
00:10:55,951 --> 00:10:58,044
Eyes on the screen, people.

159
00:10:59,688 --> 00:11:02,054
<i>ROMEO: Thus with a kiss I die.</i>

160
00:11:05,394 --> 00:11:08,625
The Volturi are a very old,
very powerful family.

161
00:11:09,231 --> 00:11:12,860
I guess they're the closest thing
to royalty my world has.

162
00:11:13,469 --> 00:11:15,664
- Is that Carlisle?
- Yeah.

163
00:11:16,872 --> 00:11:19,067
He lived with them for a few decades.

164
00:11:19,141 --> 00:11:23,737
Described them as very refined.
No respect for human life, of course,

165
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:28,116
but a respect for the arts and the sciences,
at least.

166
00:11:29,685 --> 00:11:31,175
<i>And the law.</i>

167
00:11:32,187 --> 00:11:33,950
<i>Above all, the law.</i>

168
00:11:37,192 --> 00:11:38,955
<i>BELLA: Vampires have laws?</i>

169
00:11:40,496 --> 00:11:42,123
<i>EDWARD: Not very many.</i>

170
00:11:43,298 --> 00:11:46,131
<i>And only one that's regularly enforced.</i>

171
00:11:48,637 --> 00:11:50,104
<i>BELLA: What is it?</i>

172
00:11:51,173 --> 00:11:54,267
<i>EDWARD: That we keep the existence
of our kind a secret.</i>

173
00:11:54,710 --> 00:11:57,770
<i>We don't make spectacles of ourselves,</i>

174
00:11:59,648 --> 00:12:02,173
<i>and we don't kill conspicuously.</i>

175
00:12:06,088 --> 00:12:08,556
<i>Unless, of course, you want to die.</i>

176
00:12:18,734 --> 00:12:19,723
(SCREAMS)

177
00:12:23,038 --> 00:12:25,063
You gotta stop talking about that.

178
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:28,906
I can't even think
about someone hurting you.

179
00:12:31,513 --> 00:12:35,574
Bella, the only thing that can hurt me
is you.

180
00:12:37,953 --> 00:12:40,444
And I don't have anything else
to be afraid of.

181
00:12:40,522 --> 00:12:41,580
That's not true.

182
00:12:44,059 --> 00:12:46,789
Victoria? She'll come for me one day.

183
00:12:47,730 --> 00:12:52,224
Alice will see when she decides,
and we'll be ready.

184
00:12:52,501 --> 00:12:54,401
I could protect you

185
00:12:55,370 --> 00:12:57,133
if you change me.

186
00:12:57,806 --> 00:13:00,240
Bella, you already do protect me.

187
00:13:02,211 --> 00:13:04,202
You're my only reason

188
00:13:05,848 --> 00:13:07,611
to stay alive,

189
00:13:08,283 --> 00:13:10,114
if that's what I am.

190
00:13:12,454 --> 00:13:14,752
But it's my job to protect you.

191
00:13:15,457 --> 00:13:16,446
(BELLA SIGHS)

192
00:13:18,327 --> 00:13:21,421
From everyone except my sister.

193
00:13:21,497 --> 00:13:24,728
It's time! It's time. It's time. It's time!

194
00:13:26,201 --> 00:13:27,532
<i>(THE VIOLET HOUR</i> PLAYING)

195
00:13:27,603 --> 00:13:30,231
<i>Your lips are nettles</i>

196
00:13:30,305 --> 00:13:32,364
<i>Your tongue is wine</i>

197
00:13:32,841 --> 00:13:35,435
<i>You're left as liquid
But your body's pine</i>

198
00:13:35,511 --> 00:13:37,206
<i>DR. CULLEN: Sorry about all this.</i>

199
00:13:37,279 --> 00:13:40,112
- We tried to rein Alice in.
- As if that were even possible.

200
00:13:40,182 --> 00:13:42,673
- Happy birthday, Bella.
- Thanks.

201
00:13:45,654 --> 00:13:48,623
I found it in your bag. You mind?

202
00:13:49,358 --> 00:13:51,622
Dating an older woman. Hot.

203
00:13:52,728 --> 00:13:53,752
(SIGHS EXASPERATEDLY)

204
00:13:53,829 --> 00:13:56,059
- What?
- You first, Rosalie.

205
00:13:58,934 --> 00:14:01,994
It's a necklace. Alice picked it out.

206
00:14:02,437 --> 00:14:03,631
Thanks.

207
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:08,070
Show me the love.

208
00:14:11,780 --> 00:14:13,771
This one's from Emmett.

209
00:14:16,251 --> 00:14:18,742
Already installed it in your truck.

210
00:14:18,821 --> 00:14:20,254
Finally a decent sound system

211
00:14:20,322 --> 00:14:22,722
- for that piece of...
- Hey! Don't hate the truck.

212
00:14:22,791 --> 00:14:23,815
(ALICE LAUGHS)

213
00:14:23,892 --> 00:14:26,053
Open Esme and Carlisle's.

214
00:14:27,329 --> 00:14:29,854
<i>DR. CULLEN: Just a little something
to brighten your day.</i>

215
00:14:29,932 --> 00:14:32,901
Yes, you've been looking
kind of pale lately.

216
00:14:38,173 --> 00:14:39,162
Ow.

217
00:14:40,909 --> 00:14:42,240
Paper cut.

218
00:14:54,189 --> 00:14:55,349
(GLASS SHATTERING)

219
00:15:04,132 --> 00:15:05,121
(JASPER GROWLS)

220
00:15:07,002 --> 00:15:10,062
Jaz, Jaz. It's okay. It's just a little

221
00:15:12,474 --> 00:15:13,805
blood.

222
00:15:14,243 --> 00:15:15,232
(GASPS SOFTLY)

223
00:15:16,278 --> 00:15:18,576
(JASPER SNARLS)

224
00:15:20,315 --> 00:15:22,215
<i>DR. CULLEN: Get Jasper out of here.</i>

225
00:15:22,651 --> 00:15:23,640
(BELLA GASPS)

226
00:15:27,956 --> 00:15:30,254
I'm sorry, I can't.

227
00:15:32,561 --> 00:15:35,359
I'll have to stitch this up in my office.

228
00:15:37,666 --> 00:15:39,258
Check on Jasper.

229
00:15:40,068 --> 00:15:41,535
I'm sure he's very upset with himself,

230
00:15:41,603 --> 00:15:45,130
and I doubt he'll listen to anyone
but you right now.

231
00:15:45,207 --> 00:15:46,401
Edward.

232
00:15:53,548 --> 00:15:55,243
<i>(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY)</i>

233
00:15:57,853 --> 00:16:01,345
<i>BELLA: I never wanted to have a party.
DR. CULLEN: It's not your fault.</i>

234
00:16:03,425 --> 00:16:07,555
Jasper hasn't been away from human blood
as long as the rest of us.

235
00:16:08,297 --> 00:16:09,924
How do you do it?

236
00:16:10,899 --> 00:16:13,026
Years and years of practice.

237
00:16:13,568 --> 00:16:17,436
Did you ever think
of just doing it the easy way?

238
00:16:19,274 --> 00:16:20,332
No.

239
00:16:21,510 --> 00:16:24,946
I knew who I wanted to be.
I wanted to help people.

240
00:16:26,148 --> 00:16:29,447
It brings me happiness,
even if I am damned regardless.

241
00:16:31,954 --> 00:16:33,285
Damned?

242
00:16:34,256 --> 00:16:36,986
Like hell?

243
00:16:43,432 --> 00:16:45,866
Carlisle, you couldn't be damned.

244
00:16:46,234 --> 00:16:48,532
You couldn't. It's impossible.

245
00:16:49,037 --> 00:16:50,698
Thank you, Bella.

246
00:16:50,772 --> 00:16:54,868
You've always been very gracious about us.

247
00:16:58,947 --> 00:17:02,212
So that's it?
That's why he won't change me?

