748
00:54:34,133 --> 00:54:37,364
<i>I just wanted to hear your voice,
so no pressure.</i>

749
00:54:40,473 --> 00:54:41,906
<i>Jacob, please...</i>

750
00:54:43,843 --> 00:54:45,242
Call me.

751
00:54:45,311 --> 00:54:47,939
Okay. We should be back around 3:00.

752
00:54:52,919 --> 00:54:53,908
(SIGHS)

753
00:54:54,988 --> 00:54:56,148
Hey.

754
00:54:57,090 --> 00:54:59,081
Look, I don't have to go fishing today.

755
00:54:59,158 --> 00:55:00,591
Yes, you do.

756
00:55:00,960 --> 00:55:03,588
Yeah, you do.
Go. What are you talking about?

757
00:55:03,663 --> 00:55:05,358
Just be careful.

758
00:55:05,431 --> 00:55:06,864
Always am.

759
00:55:08,534 --> 00:55:11,059
Those bears won't get the drop on me,
Bella.

760
00:55:11,137 --> 00:55:13,128
My kung fu is strong.

761
00:55:46,372 --> 00:55:47,532
Jake!

762
00:55:48,541 --> 00:55:49,803
Hey!

763
00:55:54,647 --> 00:55:56,581
You cut your hair off?

764
00:55:59,419 --> 00:56:01,250
And got a tattoo?

765
00:56:04,590 --> 00:56:05,818
Bella.

766
00:56:05,892 --> 00:56:08,861
I thought you were too sick to come outside

767
00:56:09,796 --> 00:56:12,492
or pick up the phone when I call.

768
00:56:13,733 --> 00:56:15,064
Go away.

769
00:56:16,402 --> 00:56:17,562
What?

770
00:56:19,238 --> 00:56:20,569
Go away.

771
00:56:22,542 --> 00:56:24,737
What happened to you? What's...

772
00:56:24,811 --> 00:56:27,075
Hey! What happened?

773
00:56:30,049 --> 00:56:33,109
Did Sam get to you?
Is that what's happening?

774
00:56:33,186 --> 00:56:36,485
Sam's trying to help me. Don't blame him.

775
00:56:37,590 --> 00:56:40,058
But if you want somebody to blame,

776
00:56:40,226 --> 00:56:44,162
how about those filthy bloodsuckers
you love, the Cullens?

777
00:56:44,731 --> 00:56:46,756
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

778
00:56:51,371 --> 00:56:52,497
I don't know what you're talking about.

779
00:56:52,572 --> 00:56:55,302
No, you know exactly
what I'm talking about.

780
00:56:55,375 --> 00:56:58,139
You've been lying to everyone. Charlie.

781
00:57:00,446 --> 00:57:02,471
But you can't lie to me.

782
00:57:03,583 --> 00:57:05,744
- Not anymore, Bella.
<i>- SAM: Jacob!</i>

783
00:57:06,419 --> 00:57:07,750
Jacob!

784
00:57:13,793 --> 00:57:15,283
Look, Bella,

785
00:57:16,529 --> 00:57:18,861
we can't be friends anymore.

786
00:57:19,732 --> 00:57:23,498
(CRYING) Look, Jake,
I know that I've been hurting you.

787
00:57:25,171 --> 00:57:28,197
It's killing me. It kills me.

788
00:57:30,476 --> 00:57:33,274
I just need... Maybe give me, like,

789
00:57:33,346 --> 00:57:35,371
- some time or something.
- Look, don't.

790
00:57:36,315 --> 00:57:37,839
It's not you.

791
00:57:40,753 --> 00:57:43,654
It's not you, it's me, right? Really?

792
00:57:44,590 --> 00:57:46,922
It's true. It is me.

793
00:57:49,862 --> 00:57:51,989
I'm not good.

794
00:57:54,801 --> 00:57:57,998
I used to be a good kid.

795
00:57:59,338 --> 00:58:00,737
Not anymore.

796
00:58:01,908 --> 00:58:04,502
This doesn't even matter. All right?

797
00:58:04,811 --> 00:58:05,800
This is over.

798
00:58:05,878 --> 00:58:08,039
You can't break up with me.

799
00:58:09,982 --> 00:58:11,244
I mean...

800
00:58:12,652 --> 00:58:14,882
I mean, you're my best friend.

801
00:58:17,390 --> 00:58:19,153
You promised me.

802
00:58:20,626 --> 00:58:21,957
I know.

803
00:58:22,795 --> 00:58:25,525
I promised I wouldn't hurt you, Bella.

804
00:58:26,365 --> 00:58:28,925
And this is me keeping that promise.

805
00:58:29,702 --> 00:58:31,033
Go home

806
00:58:31,771 --> 00:58:35,207
and don't come back
or you're gonna get hurt.

807
00:58:48,721 --> 00:58:50,052
<i>BELLA: Alice,</i>

808
00:58:51,090 --> 00:58:52,580
<i>things are...</i>

809
00:58:54,227 --> 00:58:56,127
<i>Things are bad again.</i>

810
00:58:57,330 --> 00:59:00,424
<i>Without Jake, I just... I can't stand it.</i>

811
00:59:03,803 --> 00:59:06,067
<i>I don't see Edward anymore.</i>

812
00:59:07,540 --> 00:59:10,441
<i>Will it really feel like he never existed?</i>

813
00:59:17,950 --> 00:59:21,113
<i>I will find the place
where I can see him again.</i>

814
01:00:06,866 --> 01:00:08,731
(SOBBING)

815
01:00:16,409 --> 01:00:17,603
Bella.

816
01:00:18,644 --> 01:00:19,906
Laurent.

817
01:00:21,914 --> 01:00:24,405
I didn't expect to find you here.

818
01:00:26,552 --> 01:00:30,852
I went to visit the Cullens,
but the house is empty.

819
01:00:33,192 --> 01:00:35,717
I'm surprised they left you behind.

820
01:00:35,928 --> 01:00:37,919
Weren't you sort of

821
01:00:39,065 --> 01:00:40,657
a pet of theirs?

822
01:00:41,634 --> 01:00:43,192
Yeah. You could say that.

823
01:00:43,269 --> 01:00:45,601
Do the Cullens visit often?

824
01:00:50,810 --> 01:00:51,799
Lie.

825
01:00:51,877 --> 01:00:52,866
(GASPS)

826
01:00:57,416 --> 01:00:58,678
Yeah, absolutely, all the time.

827
01:00:58,784 --> 01:01:00,342
Lie better.

828
01:01:00,419 --> 01:01:03,013
I'll tell them that you stopped by.

829
01:01:03,623 --> 01:01:05,818
But I probably shouldn't

830
01:01:06,292 --> 01:01:08,954
tell Edward,

831
01:01:10,763 --> 01:01:12,128
'cause he's pretty protective.

832
01:01:12,198 --> 01:01:14,393
But he's far away, isn't he?

833
01:01:17,303 --> 01:01:19,066
Why are you here?

834
01:01:19,138 --> 01:01:23,507
I came as a favor to Victoria.

835
01:01:26,979 --> 01:01:28,503
- Victoria?
- She asked me to see

836
01:01:28,581 --> 01:01:32,210
if you were still under
the protection of the Cullens.

837
01:01:32,284 --> 01:01:35,685
Victoria feels it's only fair
to kill Edward's mate,

838
01:01:36,222 --> 01:01:37,917
given he killed hers.

839
01:01:37,990 --> 01:01:39,753
An eye for an eye.

840
01:01:40,426 --> 01:01:41,620
Threaten him.

841
01:01:41,694 --> 01:01:45,186
Edward would know who did it.
And he'd come after you.

842
01:01:46,232 --> 01:01:48,166
I don't think he will.

843
01:01:49,368 --> 01:01:52,337
After all, how much could you mean to him

844
01:01:52,772 --> 01:01:55,263
if he left you here unprotected?

845
01:01:56,542 --> 01:01:57,566
(LAURENT SIGHS)

846
01:01:57,643 --> 01:02:00,635
Victoria won't be happy
about my killing you,

847
01:02:00,713 --> 01:02:02,704
but I can't help myself.

848
01:02:03,015 --> 01:02:04,778
You are so mouth-watering.

849
01:02:04,850 --> 01:02:08,581
- Please, don't. I mean, you helped us.
- No, no, no, no.

850
01:02:08,654 --> 01:02:09,678
(SHUSHING)

851
01:02:09,755 --> 01:02:13,020
Don't be afraid. I'm doing you a kindness.

852
01:02:13,325 --> 01:02:15,987
(SOFTLY) Victoria plans on killing you
slowly,

853
01:02:17,263 --> 01:02:18,594
painfully,

854
01:02:19,565 --> 01:02:21,795
whereas I'll make it quick.

855
01:02:22,168 --> 01:02:23,533
I promise.

856
01:02:24,537 --> 01:02:26,528
You will feel nothing.

857
01:02:32,278 --> 01:02:33,905
Edward, I love you.

858
01:02:33,979 --> 01:02:34,968
(TWIGS SNAPPING)

859
01:02:36,282 --> 01:02:37,977
I don't believe it.

860
01:02:38,050 --> 01:02:39,813
(LOW GROWLING)

861
01:03:02,541 --> 01:03:04,008
(ROARS)

862
01:03:12,918 --> 01:03:13,907
(GASPS)

863
01:03:34,707 --> 01:03:36,698
(WEREWOLVES RUNNING)

864
01:03:37,710 --> 01:03:38,836
(YELPING)

865
01:03:41,680 --> 01:03:42,669
(GASPS)

866
01:03:45,017 --> 01:03:47,577
- Dad! I saw them.
- What's the matter?

867
01:03:47,653 --> 01:03:50,679
- In the woods. They're not bears.
- What do you mean "in the woods"?

868
01:03:50,756 --> 01:03:52,485
Bell, what the hell
were you doing out in the woods?

869
01:03:52,558 --> 01:03:56,289
They're wolves.
I mean, they're like huge wolves.

870
01:03:56,362 --> 01:03:58,227
Are you sure about that, Bella?

871
01:03:58,297 --> 01:04:01,528
Yeah! I just saw them.
They were after something.

872
01:04:01,600 --> 01:04:02,624
(HARRY CLEARS THROAT)

873
01:04:02,701 --> 01:04:03,929
Wolves?

874
01:04:05,104 --> 01:04:06,571
You saw them?

875
01:04:09,208 --> 01:04:11,768
All right, well, Harry,

876
01:04:13,045 --> 01:04:16,378
feel like going hunting?
Get some of your guys together?

877
01:04:16,849 --> 01:04:18,874
Sure, yeah, I'll just...

878
01:04:20,653 --> 01:04:22,484
<i>BELLA: By now, those wolves will be dead,</i>

879
01:04:24,089 --> 01:04:27,149
<i>and Laurent would have told her
I'm unprotected.</i>

880
01:04:27,226 --> 01:04:28,488
<i>Victoria.</i>

881
01:04:30,229 --> 01:04:31,719
I should go to the station.

882
01:04:31,797 --> 01:04:34,231
Yeah, you should. You should go.

883
01:04:34,867 --> 01:04:37,233
<i>CHARLIE: Can you just stay in the house?</i>

884
01:04:39,805 --> 01:04:40,737
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

885
01:04:43,275 --> 01:04:44,401
(CLATTERING)

886
01:04:53,118 --> 01:04:54,107
(CLATTERING CONTINUES)

887
01:05:02,261 --> 01:05:03,523
<i>JACOB: (WHISPERS) Bella!</i>

888
01:05:06,198 --> 01:05:07,631
You scared me.

889
01:05:07,700 --> 01:05:11,158
- What the hell are you doing?
- Back up. I'm coming up.

890
01:05:19,111 --> 01:05:20,100
(GASPS)

891
01:05:23,415 --> 01:05:24,609
Hey.

892
01:05:26,785 --> 01:05:28,480
Look, I'm sorry.

893
01:05:35,561 --> 01:05:37,859
- For what?
- I wish I could explain.

894
01:05:37,930 --> 01:05:41,093
But I literally can't.

895
01:05:42,801 --> 01:05:43,790
(SIGHS)

896
01:05:49,842 --> 01:05:53,209
Have you ever had a secret
you couldn't tell anyone,

897
01:05:54,146 --> 01:05:56,614
one that wasn't yours to share?

898
01:05:59,518 --> 01:06:02,043
Well, that's what it's like for me.

899
01:06:02,321 --> 01:06:03,652
But worse.

900
01:06:05,024 --> 01:06:08,425
You have no idea how tight I'm bound.

901
01:06:09,595 --> 01:06:11,028
I hate this.

902
01:06:11,964 --> 01:06:13,955
I hate what they've done to you.

903
01:06:28,447 --> 01:06:31,507
I mean, the killer part is,
you already know.

904
01:06:35,587 --> 01:06:40,320
Bella, do you remember
when we walked on the beach at La Push?

905
01:06:41,860 --> 01:06:43,157
The...

906
01:06:47,166 --> 01:06:49,828
The story. The story about

907
01:06:51,136 --> 01:06:52,763
the cold ones.

908
01:06:54,506 --> 01:06:58,237
I guess I understand
why that's the only part you remember.

909
01:07:05,250 --> 01:07:09,118
There's gotta be something that you can do.

910
01:07:09,188 --> 01:07:11,213
No. I'm in it for life.

911
01:07:12,624 --> 01:07:15,286
Well, maybe we should just
get out of here for a while.

912
01:07:15,361 --> 01:07:17,226
Just leave,

913
01:07:17,296 --> 01:07:18,923
just you and me.

914
01:07:19,365 --> 01:07:20,957
You'd do that?

915
01:07:24,103 --> 01:07:26,071
I would do it for you.

916
01:07:32,344 --> 01:07:35,711
It's not something
I can just run away from, Bella.

917
01:07:36,648 --> 01:07:40,140
But I would run away with you

918
01:07:44,423 --> 01:07:45,822
if I could.

919
01:07:49,962 --> 01:07:53,193
I gotta go.
They'll start wondering where I am.

920
01:07:57,369 --> 01:07:58,836
Come here.

921
01:08:03,108 --> 01:08:04,405
(SOFTLY) Please,

922
01:08:05,444 --> 01:08:07,241
try to remember.

923
01:08:08,847 --> 01:08:10,974
It'd be so much easier

924
01:08:12,217 --> 01:08:13,809
if you knew.

925
01:08:16,288 --> 01:08:18,779
I'll try. But, Jake...

926
01:08:19,591 --> 01:08:22,321
Jake, what are you doing? Wait, Jake.

927
01:08:24,530 --> 01:08:25,519
(GASPS)

928
01:08:29,468 --> 01:08:30,628
Jake.

929
01:08:35,441 --> 01:08:36,430
(GASPS)

930
01:08:47,519 --> 01:08:49,282
Edward, I'm scared.

931
01:08:49,855 --> 01:08:51,482
You should be.

932
01:08:56,562 --> 01:08:58,496
<i>JACOB: Really, it's just like an old story.</i>

933
01:08:58,564 --> 01:09:00,429
<i>I'm not really supposed
to say anything about it.</i>

934
01:09:00,499 --> 01:09:04,299
<i>Did you know Quileutes
are supposedly descended from wolves?</i>

935
01:09:10,109 --> 01:09:11,098
(WEREWOLF SNARLS)

936
01:09:19,151 --> 01:09:20,379
Bella?

937
01:09:20,819 --> 01:09:22,548
I need to see him.

938
01:09:23,288 --> 01:09:24,812
He's not in.

939
01:09:26,492 --> 01:09:29,791
- Okay, I'm sorry, I really need to see him.
- Bella!

940
01:09:45,777 --> 01:09:47,438
What did you do?

941
01:09:48,447 --> 01:09:49,471
- Okay, what did you do?
- Hey.

942
01:09:49,548 --> 01:09:50,947
- What did you do to him?
- Easy!

943
01:09:51,016 --> 01:09:52,074
He didn't want this.

944
01:09:52,151 --> 01:09:54,517
What did we do? What did he do?
What'd he tell you?

945
01:09:54,586 --> 01:09:56,019
- Both of you calm down.
- Nothing.

946
01:09:56,088 --> 01:09:59,182
He tells me nothing
because he's scared of you.

947
01:09:59,258 --> 01:10:01,123
(SNICKERING)

948
01:10:04,329 --> 01:10:06,263
- Too late now.
- SAM: Bella, get back!

949
01:10:06,331 --> 01:10:07,355
(PAUL GROWLING SOFTLY)

950
01:10:07,432 --> 01:10:10,162
<i>SAM: Paul, calm down, now!</i>

951
01:10:18,810 --> 01:10:20,038
Bella!

952
01:10:21,280 --> 01:10:22,406
Run!

953
01:10:25,617 --> 01:10:26,982
Jake, run!

954
01:10:31,323 --> 01:10:33,416
(GROWLING)

955
01:10:42,467 --> 01:10:43,456
(WHIMPERS)

956
01:10:48,340 --> 01:10:50,808
(BOTH SNARLING)

957
01:10:53,178 --> 01:10:54,338
<i>SAM: Paul!</i>

958
01:11:04,990 --> 01:11:07,652
Hey! Take Bella back to Emily's place.

959
01:11:09,361 --> 01:11:11,761
<i>EMBRY: Guess the wolf's out of the bag.</i>

960
01:11:16,768 --> 01:11:20,636
<i>BELLA: Alice, is it possible that everything
is true?</i>

961
01:11:21,340 --> 01:11:23,740
<i>The fairy tales and horror stories?</i>

962
01:11:23,809 --> 01:11:27,370
<i>Is it possible that there isn't anything
sane or normal at all?</i>

963
01:11:27,512 --> 01:11:28,501
(BOTH WHOOP)

964
01:11:29,548 --> 01:11:31,448
Hey, I think we should go back
and see if Jacob's okay.

965
01:11:31,516 --> 01:11:34,178
I hope Paul sinks some teeth in him.
Serves him right.

966
01:11:34,253 --> 01:11:36,050
No way. Jacob's a natural.

967
01:11:36,121 --> 01:11:39,852
You see him phase on the fly?
I got five says Paul doesn't touch him.

968
01:11:39,925 --> 01:11:42,359
Come on in, Bella. We won't bite.

969
01:11:42,728 --> 01:11:44,491
Speak for yourself.

970
01:11:44,563 --> 01:11:45,587
<i>(DONE ALL WRONG</i> PLAYING)

971
01:11:45,664 --> 01:11:47,655
<i>I done me wrong</i>

972
01:11:47,733 --> 01:11:49,928
<i>And done all wrong</i>

973
01:11:51,136 --> 01:11:54,128
<i>All the wrong I've done
I'm sure I'll live quite long</i>

974
01:11:54,206 --> 01:11:58,802
Oh, hey, about Emily, Sam's fianc¨¦e?
Don't stare. It bugs Sam.

975
01:12:01,446 --> 01:12:03,141
Why would I stare?

976
01:12:03,215 --> 01:12:06,343
Are you guys hungry? Like I have to ask.

977
01:12:06,418 --> 01:12:07,851
(EMILY LAUGHING)

978
01:12:13,759 --> 01:12:15,351
Who's this?

979
01:12:15,427 --> 01:12:17,258
<i>JARED: Bella Swan. Who else?</i>

980
01:12:18,930 --> 01:12:19,954
Hmm.

981
01:12:20,032 --> 01:12:22,296
So, you're the vampire girl.

982
01:12:25,337 --> 01:12:27,396
So, you're the wolf girl.

983
01:12:30,275 --> 01:12:31,708
Guess so.

984
01:12:31,777 --> 01:12:34,337
Well, I'm engaged to one.

985
01:12:37,683 --> 01:12:42,211
Save some for your brothers.
And ladies first. Muffin?

986
01:12:43,255 --> 01:12:44,745
Sure. Thanks.

987
01:12:44,823 --> 01:12:48,315
Leave it to Jacob to find a way
around Sam's gag order.

988
01:12:49,094 --> 01:12:51,062
He didn't say anything to me.

989
01:12:51,129 --> 01:12:52,289
That's a wolf thing.

990
01:12:52,364 --> 01:12:54,855
Alpha's orders get obeyed
whether we want them to or not.

991
01:12:54,933 --> 01:12:57,197
And check it out.
We can hear each other's thoughts.

992
01:12:57,269 --> 01:13:01,137
Would you shut up?
These are trade secrets. Damn it!

993
01:13:01,440 --> 01:13:03,772
This chick runs with vampires.

994
01:13:04,776 --> 01:13:07,370
You can't really run with vampires.

995
01:13:07,646 --> 01:13:08,635
(EMILY GIGGLES)

996
01:13:09,348 --> 01:13:11,213
'Cause they're fast.

997
01:13:11,450 --> 01:13:14,214
Yeah? Well, we're faster.

998
01:13:15,654 --> 01:13:17,281
Freaked out yet?

999
01:13:19,024 --> 01:13:21,424
You're not the first monsters I've met.

1000
01:13:21,493 --> 01:13:24,326
<i>SAM: Jake's right. You're good with weird.</i>

1001
01:13:26,098 --> 01:13:27,258
Hey.

1002
01:13:31,136 --> 01:13:32,228
(EMILY GIGGLING)

1003
01:13:46,651 --> 01:13:48,016
Sorry.

1004
01:14:02,467 --> 01:14:04,332
So you're a werewolf?

1005
01:14:06,138 --> 01:14:08,538
Yeah. Last time I checked.

1006
