Such a waste.

1262
01:35:20,911 --> 01:35:22,742
I'm guessing you didn't rent this car?

1263
01:35:22,813 --> 01:35:24,872
I figured you wouldn't be opposed
to grand theft auto.

1264
01:35:24,948 --> 01:35:26,313
Not today.

1265
01:35:29,653 --> 01:35:31,314
What? What do you see?

1266
01:35:31,388 --> 01:35:33,288
They refused him.

1267
01:35:33,357 --> 01:35:35,791
- So?
- He's gonna make a scene.

1268
01:35:36,126 --> 01:35:38,924
- Show himself to the humans.
- No! When?

1269
01:35:39,997 --> 01:35:43,023
<i>ALICE: He's gonna wait until noon,
when the sun's at its highest.</i>

1270
01:35:43,100 --> 01:35:44,089
(GRUNTS)

1271
01:35:45,803 --> 01:35:46,997
God, Alice, you got to hurry up.

1272
01:35:47,071 --> 01:35:48,971
There's Volterra.

1273
01:35:59,183 --> 01:36:00,172
(HORN HONKING)

1274
01:36:02,786 --> 01:36:03,775
(TIRES SQUEALING)

1275
01:36:06,190 --> 01:36:08,385
(HONKING CONTINUES)

1276
01:36:10,527 --> 01:36:12,085
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1277
01:36:13,731 --> 01:36:16,564
- Why are they all in red?
- San Marco's Day festival.

1278
01:36:16,633 --> 01:36:19,466
They're commemorating
the expulsion of vampires from the city.

1279
01:36:19,536 --> 01:36:20,867
It's the perfect setting.

1280
01:36:20,938 --> 01:36:23,598
The Volturi will never let him get far enough
to reveal himself.

1281
01:36:23,674 --> 01:36:25,403
(PANTING) We have five minutes.

1282
01:36:25,475 --> 01:36:27,739
I know, Bella, just breathe.

1283
01:36:29,046 --> 01:36:30,604
(HORN HONKING)

1284
01:36:33,751 --> 01:36:34,740
Alice!

1285
01:36:34,818 --> 01:36:37,013
Bella, you're the only one
he can't see coming.

1286
01:36:37,087 --> 01:36:40,147
If I go, he'll read my thoughts.
He'll think I'm lying. He'll rush into it.

1287
01:36:40,924 --> 01:36:44,257
- Where do I go?
- He'll be under the clock tower. Go!

1288
01:37:11,288 --> 01:37:13,449
(CROWD CHANTING)

1289
01:37:50,460 --> 01:37:52,394
(BELL TOLLS)

1290
01:38:36,707 --> 01:38:38,038
Don't!

1291
01:38:38,108 --> 01:38:39,336
(BELLA PANTING)

1292
01:38:40,110 --> 01:38:41,270
Heaven.

1293
01:38:41,345 --> 01:38:43,006
You have to move.

1294
01:38:43,847 --> 01:38:46,611
Open your eyes. Look at me. I'm alive.

1295
01:38:47,384 --> 01:38:49,113
You have to move.

1296
01:38:49,987 --> 01:38:51,215
Bella.

1297
01:38:58,695 --> 01:39:00,788
- You're here.
- I'm here.

1298
01:39:03,667 --> 01:39:04,861
You're alive.

1299
01:39:08,338 --> 01:39:09,532
Yes.

1300
01:39:18,982 --> 01:39:21,576
I needed to make you see me once.

1301
01:39:22,619 --> 01:39:23,916
You had to know that I was alive,

1302
01:39:23,987 --> 01:39:27,115
that you didn't have
to feel guilty about anything.

1303
01:39:29,993 --> 01:39:32,587
I can let you go now.

1304
01:39:37,367 --> 01:39:39,528
I never acted out of guilt.

1305
01:39:41,972 --> 01:39:45,464
I just couldn't live in a world
where you don't exist.

1306
01:39:46,877 --> 01:39:48,902
- But you said...
- I lied.

1307
01:39:49,613 --> 01:39:52,707
I had to lie.
But you believed me so easily.

1308
01:39:58,355 --> 01:40:01,950
Because it doesn't make sense
for you to love me.

1309
01:40:04,661 --> 01:40:08,256
I mean, I'm nothing.
I'm human. I'm nothing.

1310
01:40:09,466 --> 01:40:13,027
Bella, you're everything to me.

1311
01:40:15,005 --> 01:40:16,700
You're everything.

1312
01:40:34,758 --> 01:40:35,952
(GATE OPENS)

1313
01:40:42,432 --> 01:40:44,525
I won't be needing your services after all,
gentlemen.

1314
01:40:44,601 --> 01:40:46,694
Aro wants to speak with you again.

1315
01:40:46,770 --> 01:40:47,998
No rules were broken.

1316
01:40:48,071 --> 01:40:52,269
Nonetheless, we should take this
conversation to a more appropriate venue.

1317
01:40:52,342 --> 01:40:53,604
Fine.

1318
01:40:54,911 --> 01:40:57,277
Bella, why don't you go
and enjoy the rest of the festival?

1319
01:40:57,347 --> 01:40:58,712
The girl comes with us.

1320
01:40:58,782 --> 01:41:00,477
No. You can go to hell.

1321
01:41:00,550 --> 01:41:01,539
(LOCK BREAKS)

1322
01:41:02,853 --> 01:41:04,445
Come on, guys.

1323
01:41:04,688 --> 01:41:08,089
It's a festival.
You wouldn't want to make a scene.

1324
01:41:08,925 --> 01:41:10,358
We wouldn't.

1325
01:41:10,727 --> 01:41:12,058
Enough.

1326
01:41:13,630 --> 01:41:14,756
Jane.

1327
01:41:15,565 --> 01:41:18,557
Aro sent me to see what was taking so long.

1328
01:41:26,610 --> 01:41:28,578
Just do as she says.

1329
01:41:41,158 --> 01:41:42,523
Go ahead.

1330
01:41:46,530 --> 01:41:48,191
Don't be scared.

1331
01:41:49,132 --> 01:41:50,463
Are you?

1332
01:41:51,435 --> 01:41:52,527
No.

1333
01:41:52,602 --> 01:41:53,591
(JANE SCOFFS)

1334
01:42:07,984 --> 01:42:10,578
<i>(OPERA PLAYING)</i>

1335
01:42:24,768 --> 01:42:26,565
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1336
01:42:31,108 --> 01:42:33,235
- Is she human?
- Yes.

1337
01:42:36,413 --> 01:42:38,040
Does she know?

1338
01:42:38,515 --> 01:42:39,675
Yes.

1339
01:42:40,050 --> 01:42:41,813
Then, why would...

1340
01:42:43,453 --> 01:42:45,250
She wants to be.

1341
01:42:45,722 --> 01:42:47,121
And so she will be.

1342
01:42:47,190 --> 01:42:48,623
Or dessert.

1343
01:42:57,134 --> 01:43:00,934
<i>ALEC: Sister. They send you out to get one
and you bring back two.</i>

1344
01:43:01,671 --> 01:43:03,138
And a half.

1345
01:43:04,307 --> 01:43:05,706
Such a clever girl.

1346
01:43:05,775 --> 01:43:07,675
What a happy surprise!

1347
01:43:08,745 --> 01:43:11,373
Bella is alive after all.

1348
01:43:12,282 --> 01:43:14,944
Isn't that wonderful?

1349
01:43:16,052 --> 01:43:17,952
I love a happy ending.

1350
01:43:19,055 --> 01:43:20,044
<i>ARO: Ah.</i>

1351
01:43:20,123 --> 01:43:21,112
(GASPS)

1352
01:43:22,392 --> 01:43:24,223
They are so rare.

1353
01:43:26,263 --> 01:43:27,252
(GASPS)

1354
01:43:28,465 --> 01:43:30,126
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1355
01:43:31,067 --> 01:43:33,592
Her blood appeals to you so much

1356
01:43:34,871 --> 01:43:36,702
it makes me thirsty.

1357
01:43:36,973 --> 01:43:39,737
How can you stand to be so close to her?

1358
01:43:39,943 --> 01:43:42,935
- It's not without difficulty.
- Yes, I can see that.

1359
01:43:43,013 --> 01:43:44,207
(ARO CHUCKLING)

1360
01:43:46,349 --> 01:43:49,910
Aro can read every thought
I've ever had with one touch.

1361
01:43:50,954 --> 01:43:53,149
And now you know everything.

1362
01:43:53,790 --> 01:43:55,553
So get on with it.

1363
01:43:58,695 --> 01:44:01,892
You are quite a soul reader yourself,
Edward.

1364
01:44:03,533 --> 01:44:07,799
Though you can't read Bella's thoughts.

1365
01:44:11,208 --> 01:44:12,675
Fascinating.

1366
01:44:16,213 --> 01:44:21,883
I would love to see
if you are an exception to my gifts, as well.

1367
01:44:24,321 --> 01:44:26,448
Would you do me the honor?

1368
01:44:47,310 --> 01:44:48,743
Interesting.

1369
01:44:49,112 --> 01:44:50,101
Hmm.

1370
01:44:50,914 --> 01:44:52,506
I see nothing.

1371
01:45:01,858 --> 01:45:03,382
I wonder if...

1372
01:45:04,227 --> 01:45:07,196
Let us see if she's immune
to all our powers.

1373
01:45:08,765 --> 01:45:10,232
Shall we, Jane?

1374
01:45:12,102 --> 01:45:13,831
- No!
- Pain.

1375
01:45:15,038 --> 01:45:16,266
(GROANS)

1376
01:45:29,886 --> 01:45:31,217
<i>BELLA: Stop!</i>

1377
01:45:32,055 --> 01:45:33,784
Stop! Please! Stop!

1378
01:45:33,857 --> 01:45:37,725
(GRUNTS) Stop! Just stop hurting him!
Please! Please!

1379
01:45:39,429 --> 01:45:40,657
Jane?

1380
01:45:42,766 --> 01:45:43,755
Master?

1381
01:45:43,833 --> 01:45:44,822
(GASPS)

1382
01:45:48,338 --> 01:45:50,067
Go ahead, my dear.

1383
01:45:55,578 --> 01:45:57,773
This may hurt just a little.

1384
01:46:10,026 --> 01:46:12,358
(LAUGHING EXCITEDLY)

1385
01:46:13,930 --> 01:46:15,397
Remarkable!

1386
01:46:17,634 --> 01:46:19,864
She confounds us all.

1387
01:46:20,904 --> 01:46:24,101
So what do we do with you now?

1388
01:46:24,641 --> 01:46:27,735
You already know
what you're going to do, Aro.

1389
01:46:28,745 --> 01:46:30,610
She knows too much.

1390
01:46:31,147 --> 01:46:32,910
She's a liability.

1391
01:46:34,284 --> 01:46:35,273
Hmm.

1392
01:46:36,886 --> 01:46:38,444
That's true.

1393
01:46:42,325 --> 01:46:43,587
Felix?

1394
01:46:47,497 --> 01:46:48,555
<i>EDWARD: No!</i>

1395
01:47:21,431 --> 01:47:22,420
(GASPS)

1396
01:47:50,126 --> 01:47:53,220
Please! No! No! Please, please!

1397
01:47:56,099 --> 01:47:59,227
Kill me! Kill me! Not him.

1398
01:48:10,246 --> 01:48:12,771
How extraordinary.

1399
01:48:14,484 --> 01:48:18,921
You would give up your life
for someone like us.

1400
01:48:20,023 --> 01:48:21,388
A vampire.

1401
01:48:22,792 --> 01:48:25,226
A soulless monster.

1402
01:48:25,295 --> 01:48:27,286
Just get away from her!

1403
01:48:31,401 --> 01:48:35,838
You don't know a thing about his soul.

1404
01:48:37,640 --> 01:48:43,442
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1405
01:48:47,450 --> 01:48:49,145
This is a sadness.

1406
01:48:51,287 --> 01:48:54,848
If only it were your intention
to give her immortality.

1407
01:49:03,766 --> 01:49:05,028
Wait!

1408
01:49:06,669 --> 01:49:08,762
Bella will be one of us.

1409
01:49:10,473 --> 01:49:11,963
I've seen it.

1410
01:49:13,743 --> 01:49:15,677
I'll change her myself.

1411
01:49:49,579 --> 01:49:51,069
Mesmerizing.

1412
01:49:51,514 --> 01:49:55,917
To see what you have seen
before it has happened.

1413
01:49:58,855 --> 01:50:03,315
Your gifts will make for an intriguing

1414
01:50:04,561 --> 01:50:05,994
immortal,

1415
01:50:07,063 --> 01:50:08,587
Isabella.

1416
01:50:13,469 --> 01:50:14,902
Go now.

1417
01:50:15,605 --> 01:50:17,573
Make your preparations.

1418
01:50:18,374 --> 01:50:20,365
Let us be done with this.

1419
01:50:22,211 --> 01:50:24,475
Heidi will arrive any moment.

1420
01:50:26,349 --> 01:50:29,750
Thank you for your visit.

1421
01:50:29,819 --> 01:50:31,377
<i>CAIUS: We will return the favor.</i>

1422
01:50:31,454 --> 01:50:34,423
I would advise that you follow through
on your promise soon.

1423
01:50:34,490 --> 01:50:36,856
We do not offer second chances.

1424
01:50:38,494 --> 01:50:41,588
<i>ARO: Goodbye, my young friends.</i>

1425
01:50:46,869 --> 01:50:47,893
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1426
01:50:47,971 --> 01:50:49,802
<i>DEMETRl: Nice fishing, Heidi.</i>

1427
01:50:49,872 --> 01:50:52,102
Yes, they do look rather juicy.

1428
01:50:52,175 --> 01:50:53,904
Save some for me.

1429
01:50:54,877 --> 01:50:57,675
<i>HEIDl: This way, please. Stay together.</i>

1430
01:51:06,889 --> 01:51:08,823
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1431
01:51:10,226 --> 01:51:11,124
(GASPING)

1432
01:51:11,194 --> 01:51:12,252
<i>(SCREAMS ECHOING)</i>

1433
01:51:12,328 --> 01:51:13,852
Stop! Stop!

1434
01:51:24,741 --> 01:51:26,265
You're here.

1435
01:51:28,311 --> 01:51:29,903
You can sleep.

1436
01:51:33,683 --> 01:51:36,311
I'll still be here when you wake up.

1437
01:51:39,922 --> 01:51:42,948
Bella, the only reason I left

1438
01:51:44,727 --> 01:51:47,662
was because I thought
I was protecting you.

1439
01:51:49,532 --> 01:51:51,193
I needed you

1440
01:51:51,267 --> 01:51:55,203
to have a chance at a normal, happy life.

1441
01:51:59,308 --> 01:52:01,674
It was so easy for you to leave.

1442
01:52:04,280 --> 01:52:07,943
Leaving you was the hardest thing
I've done in 100 years.

1443
01:52:10,353 --> 01:52:12,548
(SIGHING)

1444
01:52:14,724 --> 01:52:16,282
And I swear,

1445
01:52:17,627 --> 01:52:20,255
I will never fail you again.

1446
01:52:22,565 --> 01:52:24,123
I'm so sorry.

1447
01:52:26,536 --> 01:52:28,470
- Charlie's coming.
- Hey.

1448
01:52:31,607 --> 01:52:33,006
You okay?

1449
01:52:34,410 --> 01:52:35,672
I'm fine.

1450
01:52:38,781 --> 01:52:40,942
Dad, you don't have to worry.

1451
01:52:41,484 --> 01:52:43,475
You know, last time you said that,
you took off.

1452
01:52:43,553 --> 01:52:45,714
I didn't see you for three days.

1453
01:52:47,423 --> 01:52:49,323
I'm really sorry, Dad.

1454
01:52:51,094 --> 01:52:54,791
Bella, do not ever do that to me again.

1455
01:52:57,633 --> 01:52:58,725
Ever.

1456
01:53:01,537 --> 01:53:03,095
And you're grounded

1457
01:53:03,573 --> 01:53:05,700
for the rest of your life.

1458
01:53:06,876 --> 01:53:08,036
Okay.

1459
01:53:18,321 --> 01:53:21,119
I'm not technically
breaking any of his rules.

1460
01:53:24,127 --> 01:53:27,358
He did say
I couldn't take a step inside the door.

1461
01:53:27,830 --> 01:53:30,128
I came in through the window.

1462
01:53:33,770 --> 01:53:36,261
He's not gonna forgive me easily.

1463
01:53:38,741 --> 01:53:40,038
I know.

1464
01:53:42,078 --> 01:53:43,443
Can you?

1465
01:53:47,216 --> 01:53:48,774
I hope you can,

1466
01:53:49,585 --> 01:53:52,782
'cause I honestly don't know
how to live without you.

1467
01:53:57,126 --> 01:53:58,525
Come here.

1468
01:54:16,179 --> 01:54:19,148
Once Alice changes me,

1469
01:54:22,084 --> 01:54:24,211
you can't get rid of me.

1470
01:54:25,454 --> 01:54:27,752
She won't need to change you.

1471
01:54:28,357 --> 01:54:31,849
There are always ways
to keep the Volturi in the dark.

1472
01:54:33,563 --> 01:54:35,963
No. No.

1473
01:54:42,738 --> 01:54:44,729
You all know what I want.

1474
01:54:46,943 --> 01:54:49,912
And I know how much I'm asking for.

1475
01:54:52,181 --> 01:54:55,673
The only thing that I can think of
for it to be fair is to just vote.

1476
01:54:55,751 --> 01:54:59,118
- You don't know what you're talking about.
- Shut up.

1477
01:55:00,723 --> 01:55:01,917
Alice?

1478
01:55:02,391 --> 01:55:04,951
I already consider you my sister.

1479
01:55:08,731 --> 01:55:10,358
- Yes.
- Thank you.

1480
01:55:10,433 --> 01:55:11,923
<i>JASPER: I vote "yes."</i>

1481
01:55:13,369 --> 01:55:16,861
It would be nice to not
want to kill you all the time.

1482
01:55:18,741 --> 01:55:19,730
Hmm.

1483
01:55:19,876 --> 01:55:21,207
<i>ROSALIE: I'm sorry.</i>

1484
01:55:23,112 --> 01:55:26,240
I'm really sorry to both of you
for how I've acted,

1485
01:55:26,883 --> 01:55:28,942
and I'm really grateful
that you were brave enough

1486
01:55:29,018 --> 01:55:31,111
to go and save my brother.

1487
01:55:32,655 --> 01:55:36,091
But this isn't a life
I would have chosen for myself.

1488
01:55:38,628 --> 01:55:42,291
And I wish that there'd been someone
to vote "no" for me.

1489
01:55:45,201 --> 01:55:46,600
So, no.

1490
01:55:48,037 --> 01:55:49,937
I vote "Hell, yeah."

1491
01:55:51,874 --> 01:55:54,240
And we can pick a fight
with these Volturi some other way.

1492
01:55:54,310 --> 01:55:57,279
I already consider you
a part of the family.

1493
01:55:57,914 --> 01:55:59,142
Yes.

1494
01:55:59,482 --> 01:56:00,471
(DR. CULLEN SIGHS)

1495
01:56:05,021 --> 01:56:07,251
Why are you doing this to me?

1496
01:56:08,958 --> 01:56:10,323
You know what this means.

1497
01:56:10,393 --> 01:56:14,261
You've chosen not to live without her,
which leaves me no choice.

1498
01:56:14,997 --> 01:56:16,897
I won't lose my son.

1499
01:56:23,105 --> 01:56:27,132
<i>BELLA: I'll wait until after graduation
to make it easier on Charlie.</i>

1500
01:56:32,148 --> 01:56:35,083
Edward, I want you to be the one to do it.

1501
01:56:37,753 --> 01:56:38,742
(TIRES SCREECH)

1502
01:56:42,058 --> 01:56:44,151
He wants to talk to me.

1503
01:56:47,296 --> 01:56:48,923
<i>JACOB: So you're still alive for now.</i>

1504
01:56:48,998 --> 01:56:51,466
<i>EDWARD: He thinks it's me keeping
you away.</i>

1505
01:56:51,534 --> 01:56:54,025
<i>JACOB: You stay the hell out of my head.</i>

1506
01:56:55,137 --> 01:56:58,629
Jacob, I know you have something
to say to me.

1507
01:57:00,977 --> 01:57:04,879
But I want to say something to you first,
if that's all right.

1508
01:57:06,015 --> 01:57:07,414
Thank you.

1509
01:57:10,553 --> 01:57:13,954
Thank you for keeping Bella alive
when I didn't.

1510
01:57:14,490 --> 01:57:16,583
No. You didn't.

1511
01:57:18,594 --> 01:57:21,256
And it wasn't for your benefit, trust me.

1512
01:57:21,330 --> 01:57:23,195
I'm still grateful.

1513
01:57:23,766 --> 01:57:24,994
But I'm here now.

1514
01:57:25,067 --> 01:57:27,797
I'm not gonna leave her side
until she orders me away.

1515
01:57:27,870 --> 01:57:29,201
We'll see.

1516
01:57:32,074 --> 01:57:34,235
Hey, my turn to talk.

1517
01:57:38,814 --> 01:57:42,341
I'm here to remind you
about a key point in the treaty.

1518
01:57:42,518 --> 01:57:44,383
